OL,6,FTurning to bad character evidence, the
OL,7,Fjudge pointed out that Smyth had a
OL,8,Fprevious conviction for murder. He
OL,9,Fsaid this showed he was "happy to
OL,10,Fmurder Catholics for being Catholics".
OL,12,FDealing with the evidence given by
OL,13,FHaggarty, the judge said he was a
OL,14,F"deeply flawed individual" who had
OL,15,Fshown he was prepared to lie.
OL,17,FHe also said he had difficulty in
OL,18,Freconciling some of Haggarty's
OL,19,Fevidence with independent evidence.
